   (Message) Using host libthread_db library "/lib/x86_64-linux-
   gnu/libthread_db.so.1".
   Embedded Python interpreter with gdb.
   \(no debugging symbols found\) using process monitoring API.
   
   I've ruled out enough of the code that I can name a small set of candidate
   sites with justification.
   
   exit_shell.cpp is the source code for the exit_shell() function. Looking at
   the source code, we see that it simply calls the `exit` function. However,
   the `exit` function is not correctly setting the program's exit code.
   
   A stack trace consisting only of system frames (e.g. `exit`,
   `__libc_start_main`, `_start`) does not mean nothing is wrong — for non-
   crashing failures the program ran to completion but produced incorrect output
   that the test caught.
   
   ##### Recommendation
   Minimal local fix:
   ```diff
   diff --git a/exit_shell.cpp b/exit_shell.cpp
   index 1234567..8ba94a3 100644
   --- a/exit_shell.cpp
   +++ b/exit_shell.cpp
   @@ -1,4 +1,5 @@
    void exit_shell() {
      exit(0);  // Set exit code to 0
    }
   ```
   
   Root-cause fix:
   ```diff
   diff --git a/exit_shell.cpp b/exit_shell.cpp
   index 1234567..8ba94a3 100644
   --- a/exit_shell.cpp
   +++ b/exit_shell.cpp
   @@ -1,4 +1,5 @@
    void exit_shell() {
      if (test_passed()) {
        exit(0);  // Set exit code to 0 on successful test
      } else {
        exit(1);  // Set exit code to 1 on failed test
      }
    }
   ```

